MARC GAGE IS A FORMER
 TELEVISION NEWS REPORTER

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:35.000
EKING OUT A LIVING AS A
 FREELANCE COMMUNICATIONS

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:39.000
CONSULTANT IN VANCOUVER.
 HE'S ALSO A SINGLE FATHER,

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:42.000
ALTHOUGH IT WAS NOT
 SOMETHING HE EXPECTED.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:47.000
THE MOTHER OF MY CHILD IS AN
OLD FRIEND FROM HIGH SCHOOL.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:51.000
AND OVER THE COURSE OF TIME,
WE'VE COME TOGETHER FOR ONE

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:54.000
THING OR ANOTHER. AND THEN ONE
DARK AND STORMY NIGHT, BACK IN

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:57.000
NOVEMBER OF 1991, I WAS
DOWN THERE ON ASSIGNMENT,

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:01.000
WE GOT TOGETHER. ONE OF
THOSE EVENINGS, AS THEY SAY.

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:04.000
SHE CALLED ME TO TELL ME THAT
SHE HAD MY BABY DAUGHTER.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:09.000
WE HAD A LENGTHY DISCUSSION
AS TO WHY I WASN'T TOLD!

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:11.000
AND SHE SAID, "WELL, I JUST
DIDN'T WANNA TELL YOU.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:15.000
AND I DIDN'T WANNA TELL ANYBODY.
AND I PLACED THE CHILD FOR

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:17.000
ADOPTION AND THERE'LL BE A
NUMBER OF BITS AND PIECES OF

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:21.000
PAPER COMING YOUR WAY. BECAUSE
LEGALLY YOU HAVE TO SIGN OFF

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:24.000
ON THE DOTTED LINE, GIVING
PERMISSION FOR THE CHILD TO BE

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.000
ADOPTED." AND I SAID, "WELL,
LET'S JUST THINK ABOUT THIS FOR

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.000
HALF A SECOND." AND SHE
SUGGESTED I THINK ABOUT IT

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:33.000
AND CALL HER BACK IN A FEW DAYS.
AND I DID. AND I CALLED HER BACK

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:36.000
AND I SAID, "LOOK I'VE THOUGHT
ABOUT THIS AND THERE ARE TWO

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
OPTIONS. ONE - YOU RAISE THE
CHILD AND I PAY. OR B, I BRING

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
THE CHILD TO B.C." AND SHE SAID,
"NO. NO. THE BABY HAS BEEN

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:48.000
PLACED. THE ADOPTIVE COUPLE HAVE
BEEN SELECTED AND THEY'RE SIMPLY

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:51.000
WAITING FOR YOU TO SIGN
OFF ON THE DOTTED LINE."

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:53.000
AND I SAID,
"I'M NOT DOING IT."

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:59.000
THE ADOPTION AGENCY WAS
CALLED JEWELS FOR JESUS.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:02.000
QUITE A RELIGIOUS, CHRISTIAN,
BORN AGAIN ORGANIZATION AND

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:06.000
THEY HAD PICKED A CHRISTIAN
FAMILY FOR THE CHILD AND AS

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:10.000
A MATTER OF FACT, UNBEKNOWNST TO
ME, THE MOTHER AND THE FATHER

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:14.000
ADOPTEES HAD ALREADY STARTED TO
VISIT KELSEY AND THEY WERE JUST

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:17.000
WAITING FOR ME TO COME
IN AND SIGN OFF ON IT.

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:21.000
AND SHE TRIED EVERYTHING. SHE
WAS QUITE PERSUASIVE BUT SHE -

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:26.000
THERE WAS NO BLOODY WAY I WAS
CHANGING MY MIND. END OF STORY.

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:30.000
THERE'S NO HYPOTHETICAL IN
THIS EQUATION, AS FAR AS I'M

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:33.000
CONCERNED. YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT
THE HELL YOU WOULD DO UNLESS

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:37.000
YOU'RE CONFRONTED WITH IT,
BOTTOM LINE. SOMETHING INSIDE MY

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:40.000
BRAIN SAID, "YOU CAN'T GIVE
AWAY YOUR FLESH AND BLOOD".

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:42.000
(Narrator) AND SO
 THEIR JOURNEY BEGAN.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:46.000
MARC HAD AN INFANT DAUGHTER
 AND KELSEY HAD A SINGLE DAD.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.000
(Marc) I THOUGHT, "FEW DIAPERS,
A LITTLE BIT OF FORMULA,

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:53.000
A LITTLE BIT OF FOOD, BURPING,
WHAT THE HELL, PIECE OF CAKE,

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:57.000
ANY IDIOT CAN DO IT, RIGHT?"
WRONG! FOR THE FIRST 18 MONTHS,

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:00.000
TWO YEARS, IT WAS HELL. IT WAS
REALLY DIFFICULT TO BALANCE YOUR

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:03.000
LIFE, 'CAUSE I'M 40 YEARS OLD.
ALL OF A SUDDEN HERE IS AN

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:09.000
8-WEEK-OLD BABY - WHAT THE
---- AM I DOING? BUT I MEAN,

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:12.000
I MADE THE DECISION. IT WAS A
CONSCIOUS DECISION. THIS IS

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:15.000
SOMETHING I WANTED TO DO.
I JUST THOUGHT IT WOULD BE

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:17.000
A HELL OF A LOT
EASIER THAN IT WAS.

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:20.000
WHEN KELSEY CAME ALONG, I
DIDN'T KNOW THE FIRST THING

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:23.000
ABOUT PARENTING. BUT THEN KIDS
DON'T COME WITH INSTRUCTIONS.

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:26.000
AND THERE'S NO REFUNDS
AND NO RETURNS.

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:29.000
MARC HAD REMAINED FRIENDS
 WITH HIS EX-WIFE GINETTE,

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.000
WHO RAN A RESTAURANT
 OUTSIDE OF MONTREAL.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:35.000
GINETTE WOULD BECOME THE
 FIRST OF THE STAND-IN MOTHERS

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:38.000
TO FLOW IN AND
 OUT OF KELSEY'S LIFE.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:42.000
USUALLY A WOMAN GOES THROUGH
NINE MONTHS OF GETTING USED TO

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:46.000
HAVING A BABY AND THAT'S A
TRAUMA. SO CAN YOU IMAGINE

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:51.000
GIVING YOURSELF TWO WEEKS TO
DECIDE, YOU KNOW, THIS IS -

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:54.000
AM I GOING TO
DO THIS OR NOT?

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:58.000
(Marc) SHE WAS THE ONE TO WHOM
I TURNED WHEN I FIRST DECIDED

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:01.000
THAT I WAS GOING TO KEEP MY
CHILD. SO HERE'S MY EX-WIFE

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.000
COMING OUT TO VANCOUVER WITH ME
ON THE AIRPLANE FROM TORONTO TO

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:11.000
HELP ME BEGIN TO RAISE MY CHILD.
IT'S A, IT'S A - I THINK IT'S

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:14.000
A SCRIPT FOR A
MOVIE, ISN'T IT?

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:21.000
(Ginette) I THINK IT WAS A VERY,
VERY POSITIVE CHANGE FOR MARC.

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:24.000
IT MADE HIM A BETTER PERSON,
A MORE HUMAN PERSON,

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:29.000
MORE TOLERANT, MORE PATIENT.
THAT DOESN'T MEAN HE'S PATIENT.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.000
THAT MEANS HE'S A
LITTLE BIT MORE PATIENT.

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:35.000
THERE WAS NO DOUBT IN MY MIND
HE WOULD TAKE KELSEY -

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:38.000
NO DOUBT WHATSOEVER.

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:41.000
I THINK IT WAS THE
RIGHT DECISION.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:44.000
MARC ALSO RELIED
 ON HIS FAMILY.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:48.000
HIS SISTER KELLY MOVED IN
 DURING THE EARLY YEARS.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:56.000
(Kelly) I SAW MARC WITH KELSEY
AND, AND FIGURED THAT HE ALSO

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
NEEDED MY HELP. SHE'S TAPPED
INTO HIS MATERNAL SIDE, IF YOU

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
WILL. HE SHOWS AFFECTION
OPENLY, WHEREAS BEFORE

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:07.000
HE DIDN'T REALLY DO THAT.

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:11.000
(Marc) FROM A DISTANCE IT LOOKS
PRETTY EASY, YOU KNOW, I THOUGHT

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:14.000
IT WOULD BE PRETTY EASY. I
MEAN, IT WAS REALLY STRESSFUL,

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:17.000
SO STRESSFUL I WENT TO MY DOCTOR
AND I SAID, "SOMETIMES I THINK

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:21.000
I'M GONNA KILL THE KID. OR KILL
MYSELF. OR KILL BOTH OF US."

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:24.000
AND HE SAYS, "WELL, YOU'RE
NOT GOING TO DO THAT BECAUSE

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:26.000
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT IT. PEOPLE
WHO GENERALLY DO THAT SHOW NO

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:29.000
WARNING." HE SAYS, "HOWEVER, GO
AND TALK TO THIS PSYCHOLOGIST".

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.000
AND I THOUGHT, "OH CHRIST, A
PSYCHOLOGIST - I'M A WACKO."

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:34.000
HE SAYS, "NO, NO, NO, YOU'RE NOT
A WACKO." HE SAYS, "BUT THEY

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:37.000
WILL - SHE'LL HELP
YOU THROUGH IT. "

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:39.000
(Narrator) AS THE YEARS WORE
 ON FOR MARC AND KELSEY GAGE,

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:42.000
IT BECAME MORE AND MORE
 JUST THE TWO OF THEM.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:46.000
A SINGLE DAD WITH HIS SEVEN
 AND A HALF YEAR OLD DAUGHTER.

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:51.000
(Kelsey) CAN YOU GET ME
A STARBUCKS CAPPUCCINO?

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:52.000
I CANNOT.

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:53.000
WHY?

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:54.000
BECAUSE.

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:56.000
YOU SAID YOU WOULD.

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.000
IN THE SUMMER.

00:06:57.000 --> 00:07:00.000
(Marc) I AM THE MOST UNLIKELY
CANDIDATE FOR PARENTHOOD THAT

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
YOU WILL EVER MEET. ANYBODY WHO
KNOWS ME AND HEARD WHAT I HAD

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:07.000
DONE, THOUGHT THEY WERE HEARING
THINGS. THEY THOUGHT IT WAS

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:10.000
A JOKE. BECAUSE, I MEAN,
I DIDN'T WANT KIDS.

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:14.000
IT WASN'T PART OF THE EQUATION,
IT WASN'T GOING TO HAPPEN.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.000
YOU HAVE TO TAKE
MORE THAN TWO.

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:17.000
WHY?

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.000
BECAUSE WE NEED
MORE THAN TWO.

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:20.000
WHY?

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.000
TWO'S NOTHING, YOU
NEED NOURISHMENT,

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:25.000
YOU NEED TO EAT
VEGETABLES OR YOUR
TEETH WILL FALL OUT.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:26.000
OH, DAD.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:29.000
SHE WANTS ME TO CUT THE CRUSTS
OFF BECAUSE SHE DOESN'T LIKE

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:32.000
THE CRUSTS. CRUSTS ARE
GOOD FOR YOUR TEETH.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.000
OH OKAY, OKAY I
HEARD YOU 1,000...

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:37.000
DO YOU WANT YOUR
TEETH TO FALL OUT?

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:40.000
YOU'RE WEIRD,
BUT I STILL LIKE YOU.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
OH DADDY, DADDY, CAN WE
GO IN THE PLAYGROUND?

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:51.000
MARC'S WORK HAS BEEN
 FREELANCE AND IRREGULAR.

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:54.000
WHILE WAITING FOR A JOB
 OVERSEAS, HE DECIDED NOT TO

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.000
LEASE AN APARTMENT BUT INSTEAD
 LIVE WITH VARIOUS FRIENDS

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:00.000
FOR SHORT PERIODS. BUT
 IT'S BEEN TWO YEARS NOW,

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:03.000
AND HE AND KELSEY HAVE CAMPED
 OUT IN SEVEN DIFFERENT

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:05.000
APARTMENTS. THEY'RE
 CURRENTLY SHARING A TINY

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:08.000
CONDO WITH MARILYN,
 A FRIEND OF MARC'S.

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.000
HERE WE ARE.
ARE YOU READY?

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:14.000
YES, YES.

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:18.000
IT'S, SHALL WE SAY, IT'S SMALL.
BUT SHE'S GOT A GOOD HEART

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:20.000
AND SO SHE'S LOOKING AFTER US
UNTIL I FIGURE OUT WHAT THE

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:23.000
HELL I'M GOING TO DO WITH MY
LIFE. I MEAN, SHE'S A SEVEN AND

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:26.000
A HALF YEAR OLD LITTLE GIRL
WITH LOTS OF ENERGY. AND SO,

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.000
QUITE FRANKLY, WE DON'T
SPEND A LOT OF TIME IN HERE.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:32.000
I MEAN, SHE COMES HOME FROM
SCHOOL, SHE HAS HER BATH, GOES

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
TO SLEEP AND THEN UP AND GONE.
AND SHE GOES TO BROWNIES,

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:40.000
SHE GOES TO KARATE. SHE'S OUT
PLAYING WITH HER FRIENDS.

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:45.000
THANK GOD THE WEATHER HERE IN
BRITISH COLUMBIA IS CONDUCIVE

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:49.000
TO BEING OUTSIDE MORE THAN IT
IS IN THE REST OF THE COUNTRY

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:52.000
DURING WHAT THEY CALL "WINTER".

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:57.000
I PUT EVERYTHING IN STORAGE
BECAUSE I DIDN'T KNOW IF I'D BE

00:08:57.000 --> 00:09:00.000
COMING BACK HERE. AND BECAUSE
I'M NOT REALLY SETTLED YET,

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:03.000
I DECIDED TO LEAVE EVERYTHING
IN STORAGE - IT'S MUCH CHEAPER

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:06.000
TO PAY A HUNDRED A MONTH, THEN
1200 A MONTH AND HAVING TO PUT

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:08.000
IT ALL BACK AGAIN.

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:13.000
(*)

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:16.000
SHE'S ASKED ME A COUPLE OF
TIMES WHEN WE'RE GOING TO GET

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:18.000
OUR OWN PLACE, AND I SAID,
"WHEN DADDY FIGURES OUT WHAT IT

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:21.000
IS HE'S GOING TO DO, WE'LL
GET A PLACE TO LIVE".

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:27.000
(*)

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:31.000
I'M GRATEFUL FOR HAVING A
NUMBER OF FRIENDS WHO'VE OFFERED

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:34.000
ME A ROOF OVER MY HEAD INSTEAD
OF A DUMPSTER IN AN ALLEY.

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:37.000
JESUS CHRIST,
THAT'S ENOUGH!

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:44.000
SO I'M STAYING WITH A FRIEND
UNTIL I BASICALLY DECIDE WHAT

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.000
I'M GOING TO DO WHEN I GROW UP.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:49.000
WHAT IF YOU HAD
SLIPPED? HEAD SPLATTED
ON THE GROUND?!

00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:53.000
SCRUB THE BODY,
SCRUB THE BODY.

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:56.000
I DON'T ADVOCATE DOING THIS.
THIS IS NOT THE WAY TO DO IT.

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:59.000
TWO PARENT FAMILIES ARE MUCH,
MUCH BETTER. MUCH BETTER.

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:03.000
THIS SINGLE PARENT STUFF IS -
WHILE IT MAY BE NOVEL AND IT

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:06.000
MAY BE INTERESTING,
IT'S NOT THE WAY TO GO.

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:08.000
I'M LOOKING FOR NITS,
DO WE SEE ANY NITS IN HERE?

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:10.000
(Kelsey) GOD DAD,
YOU'RE WEIRD.

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:12.000
(Marc) LICE.

00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:16.000
DID YOU GO LIKE THIS?

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:18.000
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:19.000
EWWW, GROSS!

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:23.000
AS KELSEY NEARED HER
 EIGHTH BIRTHDAY,

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:26.000
SHE WAS BECOMING MORE
 CURIOUS ABOUT THINGS THAT

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:28.000
WERE MISSING IN HER LIFE.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:30.000
INTO THE SACK.

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:34.000
SHE KNOWS HER MOTHER EXISTS,
SHE KNOWS SHE LIVES IN ONTARIO

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:36.000
AND SHE KNOWS SHE
HAS A HALF-BROTHER.

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:39.000
I'LL SEE YOU IN
THE MORNING, OKAY?

00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:43.000
AND SO MARC GAGE DECIDED IT
 WAS TIME TO TAKE HIS DAUGHTER

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:45.000
TO TORONTO.

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
(Kelsey) YES, AND HERE'S AN
UGLY LOOKING MAN NEAR THIS

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
WONDERFUL LOOKING PIECE OF ART!

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:03.000
(Marc) IT WAS KIND OF
ANTI-CLIMACTIC BECAUSE WE BANGED

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:06.000
ON THE DOOR, THE DOOR WAS OPEN,
WE WALKED DOWN THE STAIRS,

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:09.000
THERE WAS MOM AT THE BOTTOM OF
THE STAIRS. KELSEY GOES "MOMMY",

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:14.000
HUGGED HER MOMMY AND SAW THE
TWO CATS AND AWAY SHE WENT.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:19.000
SHE GAVE US ICE-CREAM
AND HER TWO CATS -

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:23.000
ONE'S LAZY AND ONE
LIKES TO BE CHASED.

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:26.000
(Marc) AND THEN HER HALF-BROTHER
CAME IN, AND THEY GOT ALONG

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:30.000
FAMOUSLY. IT WAS AS IF THEY'D,
THEY'D KNOWN EACH OTHER

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:33.000
ALL THEIR LIVES. SHE'S ALWAYS
KNOWN SHE'S HAD A MOM,

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:37.000
AND I GUESS, THIS JUST CONFIRMED
IN HER LITTLE MIND THAT THIS

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:40.000
WAS, THAT SHE REALLY DID HAVE
A MOM AND SHE WAS ABLE TO PUT

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:43.000
A FACE TO THIS ICON OF
MOTHERHOOD. THE THING THAT,

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:46.000
THAT BUGS ME, I SUPPOSE, IS
THAT, YOU KNOW, WE'VE, WE'VE

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:48.000
BEEN THERE, WE'VE DONE THAT,
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH IT BUT THE

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:51.000
PHONE HASN'T RUNG AND THERE'S
BEEN NO CORRESPONDENCE FROM

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:55.000
EITHER MOTHER OR BROTHER SO THAT
MAY... THAT MAY BE FESTERING

00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:58.000
AWAY IN HER LITTLE BRAIN. I
DON'T KNOW. THAT'S SOMETHING,

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:02.000
I SUPPOSE, THAT WE'LL HAVE TO
TALK ABOUT. BUT I'M - I'M A BIT

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:06.000
PISSED OFF THAT SHE HASN'T
TAKEN MORE OF A ROLE.

