FOR TOM NELSON OF EDMONTON,

00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:20.000
LIFE OFFERED NO SUCH
 MOMENT OF CHOICE.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:24.000
(Tom) I CAUGHT YOUR MOTHER IN
THE MORNING WHEN SHE WOKE UP.

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:26.000
(Anna) A WOMAN'S DREAM!

00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:29.000
(Tom) SHE ALWAYS HAD VERY GOOD
HUMOUR. SHE'S SMILING THERE AND

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:34.000
THAT WAS A SPLENDID TIME. ONE
OF THE TIMES WHEN YOU THINK

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:37.000
BACK IN YOUR LIFE,
THERE ARE FEW
TIMES THAT ARE,

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:40.000
SORT OF GOLDEN, OKAY.

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:43.000
TOM NELSON WAS ONLY TEN
 WHEN HIS MOTHER DIED.

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:46.000
HE WAS RAISED BY
 A SINGLE FATHER.

00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:50.000
TOM GREW TO MANHOOD, SURVIVED
 THE SECOND WORLD WAR,

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:54.000
BECAME A CAREER ACADEMIC,
 MARRIED AND HAD THREE

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:58.000
CHILDREN. IN THE SUMMER OF
 1967, HE AND HIS WIFE, JOYCE,

00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:01.000
WERE EXPECTING
 THEIR FOURTH CHILD.

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:09.000
SHE DIED IN CHILDBIRTH AND
IT WAS A TERRIBLE TRAUMA.

00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:15.000
YOU FEEL THE DIFFERENT
RESPONSIBILITY WHEN SOMETHING

00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:19.000
LIKE THAT HAPPENS.
I KNEW WHAT I HAD TO DO.

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:23.000
I'D ALREADY LIVED
THROUGH IT, YOU KNOW.

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:28.000
AND YOU TOOK CARE OF YOUR
FAMILY ONCE, AND SECONDLY YOU

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:32.000
DIDN'T GET MARRIED UNTIL
THEY NO LONGER NEEDED YOU.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:35.000
THE BOY WHO'D BEEN RAISED
 BY A SINGLE FATHER

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:39.000
WAS NOW A SINGLE DAD HIMSELF
 WITH THREE YOUNG CHILDREN.

00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:46.000
MY WIFE DIED 35 YEARS AGO, SO
I'M QUITE A DISTANCE FROM THAT

00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:52.000
EVENT NOW. BUT WHEN I THINK
ABOUT IT - AND I TRY NOT TO DO

00:15:53.000 --> 00:16:02.000
THAT - IT'S AS FRESH AS IT WAS
AT THE TIME I WAITED IN THE,

00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:05.000
IN THE HOSPITAL AND THEY
CAME OUT TO TELL ME,

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:10.000
"YOUR WIFE IS DYING, GO IN AND
SEE HER". AND I WENT IN AND

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:14.000
TALKED WITH HER. AND THEN LATER,
WHEN SHE DIED, I TOOK HER TO THE

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:19.000
MORGUE MYSELF, YOU KNOW. BUT
THOSE THINGS ARE VERY FRESH

00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:21.000
AND I TRY NOT TO THINK OF THEM

00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:25.000
BECAUSE THEY DO
YET OVERWHELM ME.

00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:30.000
THE IRONY OF JOYCE'S DEATH
 WAS NOT LOST ON TOM NELSON,

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:33.000
WHAT HIS CHILDREN WERE
 NOW GOING THROUGH,

00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:35.000
HE HIMESLF HAD EXPERIENCED.

00:16:35.000 --> 00:16:39.000
MY FATHER TOLD ME IN THE
MORNING. HE SAID, "YOUR MOTHER

00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:43.000
DIED LAST NIGHT." HE SAID, "I
TAKE CARE OF YOU NOW". HE SAID,

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:47.000
"I WANT TO TELL YOU THAT I WILL
TAKE CARE OF YOU AND I PROMISED

00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:51.000
YOUR MOTHER THAT I WOULDN'T
MARRY UNTIL YOU'RE GROWN."

00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:56.000
SO, SO THOSE WERE THE RULES
THAT WERE SET DOWN.

00:16:56.000 --> 00:17:03.000
WE ALL KNOW LIFE GOES ON. AND
YOU HAVE A SET OF OBLIGATIONS

00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:06.000
- I'VE GOT THREE CHILDREN. MY
WIFE DIED ON MY YOUNGEST CHILD'S

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:13.000
SECOND BIRTHDAY. I'VE GOT TO
DEAL WITH THE DISAPPEARANCE OF

00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:20.000
THEIR MOTHER, BECAUSE OF COURSE,
THEY RESIST THAT IDEA BECAUSE

00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:23.000
THEY HAVE NO KNOWLEDGE OF IT.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:28.000
HIS ELDEST CHILD, ANNA, IS
 NOW A HIGH SCHOOL TEACHER.

00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:30.000
SHE WAS SIX
 WHEN HER MOTHER DIED.

00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:35.000
(Anna) MY DAD NEVER LET US SULK
OR, YOU KNOW, "IT'S OKAY TO CRY

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:38.000
BUT LIKE, GET OVER IT AND LET'S
GET ON WITH THINGS, YOU KNOW."

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:42.000
AND CRYING DOESN'T SOLVE VERY
MUCH. IT MAKES YOU FEEL GOOD FOR

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:46.000
ABOUT LIKE ONE SECOND AND THEN
YOU'RE, THEN YOU'RE AN IDIOT,

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:50.000
YOU KNOW. AND, AND I DO AGREE
ABOUT THE PICTURES ON THE WALL.

00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:53.000
HE, MY DAD - WE NEVER HAD
PICTURES OUT OF MY MOTHER.

00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:57.000
AND HE NEVER REALLY
TALKED ABOUT HER.

00:17:57.000 --> 00:18:00.000
THESE ARE PICTURES,
OF COURSE, THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:03.000
YOUR CHILDHOOD,
YOU KNOW?

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:08.000
(Anna) YOU CAN'T LIVE LIFE IN
THE PAST. YOU CAN'T SIT AROUND

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:11.000
AND GO, "OH, YOU KNOW, IF YOUR
MOTHER WAS HERE TODAY, WE WOULD,

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:15.000
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH."
WELL, SHE'S NOT, SO DO IT

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:20.000
ANYWAY. AND I THINK THAT IS
SORT OF WHAT MY DAD MEANT,

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:27.000
OR HOW I TOOK IT ANYWAY. IT
ALLOWS YOU TO RECOVER, I THINK,

00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:31.000
FAIRLY QUICKLY FROM LIFE'S
LITTLE, LITTLE TROUBLES.

00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.000
AND BECAUSE YOU KNOW THAT THE
FASTER YOU DO IT, THE EASIER

00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:39.000
LIFE IS... YOU KNOW? AND THERE'S
NO POINT IN CRYING ABOUT IT

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:41.000
BECAUSE IT DOESN'T
CHANGE ANYTHING.

00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:45.000
(Tom) AFTER THE CHILDREN ARE IN
BED, I COULD WORK UNTIL ABOUT

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:49.000
TWO O'CLOCK IN THE MORNING
AND THEN GO TO BED AND,

00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:54.000
ANAESTHETIZED, GO TO SLEEP.
GET UP IN THE MORNING AT EIGHT

00:18:54.000 --> 00:18:58.000
AND... DO THE SAME THING AGAIN.

00:18:58.000 --> 00:19:01.000
LIKE EVERY OTHER FATHER,
 DR. TOM NELSON,

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:05.000
ACADEMIC PSYCHOLOGIST, DID
 NOT ESCAPE THE TRAUMA THAT

00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:08.000
COMES WITH HAVING
 A TEENAGE DAUGHTER.

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:15.000
(Tom) MY DAUGHTER. MY DAUGHTER
AND I, WE DIFFERED IN, IN A LOT

00:19:15.000 --> 00:19:20.000
OF RESPECTS. AND SHE JUST
THOUGHT I WAS PRETTY MUCH OUT

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:26.000
TO LUNCH, YOU KNOW. AND SO I
COULDN'T ACCEPT THAT KIND OF

00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:29.000
TREATMENT FROM HER. AND THERE
WAS ABOUT THREE OR FOUR YEARS

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:34.000
WHICH WE HAD VIRTUALLY NOTHING
TO DO WITH ONE ANOTHER.

00:19:34.000 --> 00:19:38.000
BUT THEN SHE NEEDED ME AT
SOME POINT, AND OF COURSE,

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:40.000
I ALWAYS NEEDED HER.

00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:44.000
THERE WAS A TIME WHEN I, I
DIDN'T WANT TO BE WITH MY DAD,

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:47.000
YOU KNOW. 'CAUSE HE WAS, HE HAD
AN OPINION ABOUT, JUST ABOUT

00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:50.000
EVERYTHING. AND HE THOUGHT HE
WAS RIGHT, AND HE TALKED IN A

00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:54.000
LOUD VOICE AND YOU KNOW,
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:57.000
AND HE DIDN'T DO THINGS THE
RIGHT WAY. AND HE USED TO WEAR

00:19:57.000 --> 00:20:03.000
THESE REALLY GARISHLY LOUD TIES
THAT - WITH CLASHING SHIRTS.

00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:06.000
AND I DIDN'T KNOW HOW I COULD
POSSIBLY WALK DOWN THE STREET

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:09.000
WITH HIM WEARING THAT. AND HE
HAD THIS BLACK SUIT - I CALLED

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:12.000
IT "THE MAFIA SUIT" - IT HAD
LIKE THIS WHITE STITCHING.

00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:14.000
I HATED THAT SUIT.

00:20:14.000 --> 00:20:19.000
I HAD BOUGHT A RED
SUEDE JACKET, YOU
KNOW HOW I WAS,

00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:22.000
I WAS ALWAYS LOOKING
FOR A BARGAIN,

00:20:22.000 --> 00:20:25.000
I GOT A TREMENDOUS
BARGAIN ON THIS
JACKET.

00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:28.000
(Anna) BUT NOW, YOU KNOW. NOW
I REALIZE THAT, YOU KNOW,

00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:32.000
IT WASN'T HIM AT ALL - IT WAS
ME. I WAS SORT OF A JERK AND...

00:20:32.000 --> 00:20:39.000
TOO, TOO YOUNG TO KNOW THE
REALITY OF LIFE. AND, YOU KNOW.

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:43.000
NOW MY DAD'S A PRETTY GOOD GUY,
SO THERE'S HOPE FOR THE FUTURE,

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:47.000
YOU KNOW. I SUPER LIKE BEING
WITH MY DAD NOW. AND - ARGUING

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:50.000
IN PUBLIC NOW IS
A FUN THING!

00:20:57.000 --> 00:21:01.000
(Tom) WHAT I WONDER ABOUT - AND
I CAN NEVER KNOW - IS WHAT

00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:09.000
THEY'RE LIKE INSIDE FROM THIS
EVENT. AND I, I WORRY ABOUT IT,

00:21:09.000 --> 00:21:16.000
BECAUSE HERE THERE ARE TWO
GENERATIONS OF MASCULINE

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:23.000
DOMINATION IN THEIR, IN THEIR
PREPARATION FOR LIFE.

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:27.000
AND I THOUGHT MORE LIKE MY
FATHER THAN I WOULD HAVE,

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:35.000
HAD MY MOTHER LIVED. AND NOW
THEY'RE GIVEN THAT AS A FATHER,

00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:37.000
WHO IS ALREADY BIASED

00:21:37.000 --> 00:21:42.000
AND NOW HAS AN ADDITIONAL
BIAS TO FIX ON THEM.

00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:47.000
(Anna) I THINK SOMETIMES MY DAD
FEELS GUILTY THAT HE WASN'T,

00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:50.000
THAT HE WASN'T MORE HUGGY
AND HE WASN'T MORE KISSY,

00:21:50.000 --> 00:21:53.000
AND HE DIDN'T GIVE US
MORE "I LOVE YOU"S,

00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:58.000
BUT THAT STUFF IS SUPERFICIAL.
YOU KNOW - ANYBODY CAN DO THAT.

00:21:58.000 --> 00:22:01.000
AND THEY DON'T EVEN HAVE TO LIKE
YOU. YOU KNOW, THOSE ARE JUST

00:22:01.000 --> 00:22:06.000
EMPTY WORDS. AND I THINK WHAT
YOU DO AND HOW YOU LIVE YOUR

00:22:06.000 --> 00:22:09.000
LIFE AND HOW YOU TREAT YOUR
CHILDREN AND THE THINGS YOU DO

00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:13.000
WITH THEM - LIKE ALL THE CAMPING
TRIPS WE WENT ON, AND THE FACT

00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:16.000
THAT HE HAD THREE CHILDREN
AND HE HAD THREE DOGS TOO.

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:19.000
AND HE HAD A FULL - YOU KNOW,
FULL-TIME JOB AND HE, HE DID

00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:22.000
ALL THAT STUFF. THAT STUFF IS,
IN RETROSPECT, YOU KNOW,

00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:25.000
IS WORTH A LOT MORE THAN ALL
THAT OTHER STUFF. ALL THAT OTHER

00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:29.000
STUFF IS JUST - IT'S GREAT, YOU
KNOW, IT'S OKAY. AND IT'S GOOD

00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:33.000
SOMETIMES. BUT IF THAT'S ALL
YOU HAVE TO BASE YOUR LIFE

00:22:33.000 --> 00:22:38.000
FOUNDATION ON,
THEN IT'S NOTHING.

00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:43.000
HERE'S ANOTHER PICTURE
THAT'S A PICTURE OF
YOU KNOW WHO!

00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:52.000
IN MY BUFFALO HAT! I
DON'T KNOW IF YOU'VE
SEEN THAT ONE EITHER.

00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:54.000
THIS IS THE SAME TIME?

00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:57.000
(Tom) YEAH, SAME
TIME, RIGHT.

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:06.000
I CALL THIS
THE GOOD DAYS,
AND THEY WERE.

00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:30.000
MY CHILDHOOD WAS GREAT, LIKE,
I DIDN'T MISS ANYTHING.

00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:35.000
AND I DID GET EVERYTHING YOU
NEED FROM, WELL, IN THIS CASE

00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:43.000
FROM MY DAD. AND YOU GROW UP TO,
TO BE SELF RELIANT AND CAN MAKE,

00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:48.000
FOR THE MOST PART, VERY SOUND
DECISIONS ABOUT YOURSELF AND,

00:23:48.000 --> 00:23:53.000
AND YOU LEARN TO, I THINK,
LIVE LIFE WITH NO REGRETS.

00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:56.000
(Tom) MY CHILDREN ARE EXTREMELY
STRONG, ALL THREE OF THEM,

00:23:57.000 --> 00:24:02.000
AS PERSONS. I HAVE TWO THAT ARE
MARRIED AND ONE IS PREPARING

00:24:02.000 --> 00:24:07.000
TO GET MARRIED. YOU KNOW, I'M SO
DELIGHTED WITH THE GRANDCHILDREN

00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:15.000
AND, AND, AND BEING IN THEIR
PRESENCE AND BEING EXCEPTED

00:24:15.000 --> 00:24:21.000
AS A PERSON WHO IS DESIRABLE
TO BE AROUND, YOU KNOW?

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:26.000
AT LEAST FOR A COUPLE
OF HOURS! (chuckles)

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:31.000
AND SOMEBODY WHO THEY WANT
THEIR CHILDREN TO KNOW.

00:24:32.000 --> 00:24:35.000
WHEN HIS CHILDREN WERE OLD
 ENOUGH TO MAKE THEIR OWN WAY

00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:38.000
IN THE WORLD, 34 YEARS
 AFTER HIS WIFE DIED,

00:24:38.000 --> 00:24:42.000
AND HE'D RETIRED AS
 DEPARTMENT HEAD OF THE
 UNIVERSITY OF ALBERTA,

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:45.000
TOM NELSON,
 IN HIS 70s, REMARRIED.

00:24:45.000 --> 00:24:49.000
HIS NEW WIFE IS HIS
 FIRST WIFE'S SISTER.

