(*)

00:24:54.000 --> 00:24:57.000
BUT ANOTHER DAD, ROSS
 HEIGHT IN SASKATCHEWAN,

00:24:57.000 --> 00:25:00.000
IS RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE OF
 THE ROLLERCOASTER RIDE

00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:02.000
OF SINGLE PARENTHOOD.

00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:09.000
(Ross) THIS IS THE WAY IT IS.
PEOPLE MIGHT LOOK AT US FUNNY

00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:13.000
OR THUMB THEIR NOSES AT ME,
THINK I'M A BURDEN ON SOCIETY,

00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:16.000
I DON'T CARE. GO AHEAD. THINK
WHAT YOU WANT. BUT I DON'T

00:25:16.000 --> 00:25:20.000
EXPECT YOU UNDERSTAND. OR DON'T
TELL ME YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE

00:25:20.000 --> 00:25:23.000
TO BE ME OR ANY OTHER SINGLE
PARENT DAD, MOM, I DON'T CARE

00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:26.000
WHAT, JUST BECAUSE YOU SAT IN
SOME SCHOOL AND READ THE BOOK.

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:29.000
DON'T TELL ME YOU
KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE.

00:25:29.000 --> 00:25:32.000
BECAUSE YOU DON'T.

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:35.000
SIX WEEKS AFTER HIS WIFE
 SUDDENLY LEFT WITH THEIR

00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:39.000
THREE CHILDREN, AND STILL NOT
 SURE WHERE THEY HAD GONE,

00:25:39.000 --> 00:25:42.000
THE BEST THING IN ROSS
 HEIGHT'S LIFE WAS HIS JOB.

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:45.000
HE WAS A LONG HAUL TRUCK
 DRIVER, LICENSED TO CARRY

00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:48.000
DANGEROUS GOODS. IT WAS A
 BIG PART OF WHO HE WAS.

00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:51.000
BUT IT CAME TO
 A SUDDEN END.

00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:56.000
(Ross) I KNEW THAT TRACK WAS
THERE - I'D BEEN OVER IT 200

00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:01.000
TIMES BEFORE. AND I DIDN'T
SEE NOTHING OUT THERE.

00:26:01.000 --> 00:26:06.000
GOT THE THING ON THE TRACKS,
FELT THE FRONT WHEELS ON THE

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:09.000
RAILS AND I JUST
LOOKED OUT THE SIDE...

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:14.000
AND THIS BIG, DAMNED
BLACK THING...

00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:19.000
IT WAS JUST BLACK
AND IT WAS HUGE.

00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:22.000
(train whistle blows)

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:33.000
A PRAIRIE THUNDER STORM,
 EXHAUSTION AND WORRY

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:36.000
WERE A DEADLY COMBINATION
 FOR ROSS THAT NIGHT.

00:26:36.000 --> 00:26:39.000
HE SURVIVED, BUT FOUND
 HIMSELF ON MEDICATION

00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:42.000
FOR THE REST OF HIS LIFE.

00:26:42.000 --> 00:26:45.000
(Ross) OBVIOUSLY I LOST MY JOB
AT KINDERSLEY OVER THAT BECAUSE

00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:48.000
THERE WAS DANGEROUS GOODS
INVOLVED AND EVERYTHING ELSE.

00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:51.000
I WENT FROM HAVING A DEDICATED
RUN, SCHEDULED DAYS OFF,

00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:55.000
TO SITTING BY THE PHONE,
WAITING FOR IT TO RING.

00:26:55.000 --> 00:26:57.000
ANOTHER BUMMER, YOU KNOW.

00:26:57.000 --> 00:27:00.000
AND EVERYTHING JUST
WENT WRONG FROM THERE ON.

00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:03.000
THAT JOB MEANT
EVERYTHING TO HIM.

00:27:03.000 --> 00:27:05.000
IT WAS A GOOD JOB.

00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:08.000
ROSS'S FRIEND,
 CAROLINE FENNER.

00:27:09.000 --> 00:27:14.000
I'M SURE IT MADE IT HARD TO
GET OTHER GOOD JOBS SO IT WAS

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:21.000
DEVASTATING TO HIS, HIS WORK,
TO HAVE HAD THAT ACCIDENT.

00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:29.000
AND I THINK IT ALSO MAYBE
MADE HIM REALIZE THAT...

00:27:29.000 --> 00:27:34.000
JUST HOW MUCH HE WAS TROUBLED
BY THE KIDS BEING GONE.

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:40.000
TO HAVE AS GOOD A DRIVER AS HE
WAS, TO ALLOW THAT TO HAPPEN.

00:27:40.000 --> 00:27:44.000
TO JUST DRIVE OVER THOSE
TRACKS AND NOT SEE THAT TRAIN.

00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:46.000
THAT'S SOMETHING HE WOULDN'T DO.

00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:49.000
HE'S TOO GOOD.

