ROSS'S WIFE HAD LEFT THEIR
 SMALL SASKATCHEWAN TOWN

00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:55.000
WITH THE THREE KIDS.

00:27:55.000 --> 00:27:58.000
(Ross) I JUST WENT HOME FROM
WORK ONE DAY AND THEY WERE GONE.

00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:02.000
SHE WENT FOR FULL CUSTODY AND
THE JUDGE DIDN'T DO THAT,

00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:05.000
BUT HE MIGHT AS WELL HAVE. WHAT
YOU GET IS JOINT CUSTODY WITH

00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:11.000
THE PRIMARY RESIDENCE BEING WITH
HER. A DIFFERENT WAY OF SAYING

00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:15.000
FULL CUSTODY. AND SHE WAS
GETTING, WHAT WAS I COUGHING UP

00:28:15.000 --> 00:28:18.000
$450 A MONTH CHILD SUPPORT. AND
THEN I'D SEND BIKE MONEY OUT,

00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:21.000
SKATEBOARD MONEY OUT
AND ALL THIS KIND OF
STUFF WHENEVER I COULD.

00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:24.000
I THINK THE LOSS OF HIS
MARRIAGE WAS DEVASTATING BUT

00:28:24.000 --> 00:28:27.000
BEING WITHOUT HIS CHILDREN
JUST ABOUT KILLED HIM.

00:28:27.000 --> 00:28:30.000
HE REALLY WAS HURTING
ABOUT THOSE CHILDREN.

00:28:30.000 --> 00:28:35.000
I'VE ONLY EVER SEEN ROSS
CRY ONCE IN HIS LIFE

00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:37.000
AND THAT WAS ABOUT THE KIDS.

00:28:37.000 --> 00:28:40.000
AND I DIDN'T GO TO COURT OR
ANYTHING LIKE THAT TO GET THE

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:47.000
KIDS BACK. I CONSIDERED IT, I
LOOKED INTO IT. BUT I MEAN,

00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:51.000
IT'S THOUSANDS AND THOUSANDS OF
DOLLARS AND INTER-PROVINCIAL

00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:56.000
LIKE THIS, THE LAWYERS ARE BIG
BUCKS. WHAT MADE IT EVEN WORSE

00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:59.000
WAS ME BEING OUT HERE, HELPLESS,
KNOWING THEY'RE WAY OUT THERE

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:02.000
AND I CAN'T DO
ANYTHING ABOUT IT.

00:29:02.000 --> 00:29:08.000
(Caroline) HE WAS HURTING SO BAD
THAT HE DIDN'T EVEN KNOW HIMSELF

00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:11.000
WHAT HE WAS THINKING OR
FEELING SOME DAYS.

00:29:11.000 --> 00:29:14.000
IT WAS SO HARD ON HIM.

00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:18.000
BEFORE LONG, HE LOST HIS
 HOUSE AND FOUND HIMSELF

00:29:18.000 --> 00:29:20.000
ON A DOWNHILL SPIRAL.

00:29:21.000 --> 00:29:26.000
IF ANYBODY WANTS TO TRADE
AND TRY IT OUT, LET ME KNOW!

00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:30.000
AND THEN 18 MONTHS AFTER
 THEY'D BEEN TAKEN AWAY,

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:33.000
HIS CHILDREN DECIDED THEY
 WANTED TO COME BACK TO

00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:37.000
SASKATCHEWAN AND LIVE
 WITH THEIR DAD.

00:29:37.000 --> 00:29:40.000
SO AT A TIME WHEN HE FELT
 HE'D REACHED THE VERY BOTTOM,

00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:44.000
ROSS HEIGHT SUDDENLY
 BECAME THE SOLE SUPPORT FOR

00:29:44.000 --> 00:29:47.000
14-YEAR-OLD JUSTIN,
 13-YEAR-OLD JESSICA

00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:51.000
AND THE BABY, SHANNON,
 WHO WAS NOW 10.

00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:54.000
(Ross) IT WASN'T A TOUGH
DECISION TO MAKE. I DIDN'T EVEN

00:29:54.000 --> 00:30:01.000
CONSIDER NOT DOING IT. SO. I
CAN'T IMAGINE CONSIDERING NOT

00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:06.000
DOING IT. THEY'RE YOUR KIDS,
FOR CHRIST'S SAKE. YOU KNOW.

00:30:10.000 --> 00:30:14.000
THERE'S LOTS OF TIMES I WAS
WORRIED SICK ABOUT FEEDING THEM

00:30:14.000 --> 00:30:19.000
AND EVERYTHING ELSE, BUT
I DO WHATEVER I CAN DO

00:30:19.000 --> 00:30:22.000
RIGHT FROM SWEEPING PARKING
LOTS, QUITE OFTEN I GOT TO GO

00:30:23.000 --> 00:30:27.000
TO SOCIAL SERVICES TO HELP US
OUT. I FEEL BAD WALKING IN THERE

00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:30.000
BUT ON THE OTHER HAND I
KNOW I GOT NO DAMN CHOICE.

00:30:31.000 --> 00:30:47.000
(*)

00:30:47.000 --> 00:30:50.000
YOU DON'T NEED LUNCH
TODAY, DO YOU?

00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:51.000
NO.

00:30:54.000 --> 00:30:56.000
KIND OF BURNT,
THOUGH, HEY DAD?

00:30:56.000 --> 00:30:58.000
DID I?

00:30:58.000 --> 00:31:01.000
KIND OF CRISPY.

00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:03.000
IT'S SUPPOSED TO
BE LIKE THAT.

00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:08.000
I HAD TO TEACH HIM HOW TO
COOK PANCAKES AND MACARONI

00:31:08.000 --> 00:31:12.000
AND GRILLED CHEESE, BUT I
ALREADY KNEW HOW TO COOK THAT.

00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:15.000
IT WAS PRETTY MUCH
AUTOMATIC FOR HIM TO
JUST COME HOME AND

00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:18.000
COOK. AND YOU KNOW,
IT JUST - HE ALWAYS
DID IT.

00:31:18.000 --> 00:31:21.000
NEVER SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT IT. NEVER
ASKED US TO DO IT.

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:30.000
WHEN HE - LIKE HE'LL BE FRYING
THE SPAGHETTI, RIGHT, 'CAUSE HE

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:34.000
DOESN'T MICROWAVE IT, HE FRIES
IT. AND THEN HE BURNS IT.

00:31:34.000 --> 00:31:37.000
AND IT'S ALL BURNT AND CRISPY
AND THEN HE MAKES ME EAT IT!

00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:40.000
THAT'S JUST GROSS.

00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:44.000
HE'S A GOOD COOK IF
HE'S COOKING MEAT
AND POTATOES.

00:31:44.000 --> 00:31:46.000
YEAH. HE'S GOOD AT
WHAT HE CAN MAKE,

00:31:46.000 --> 00:31:48.000
AND THAT'S NOT
A LOT. BUT!

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:51.000
WE'D SIT AROUND HERE AND LAUGH
AT OURSELVES, YOU KNOW -

00:31:51.000 --> 00:31:53.000
AND SOME STUPID REMARK
SOMEBODY WOULD BRING OUT.

00:31:54.000 --> 00:31:56.000
AND THEN WE'D TALK ABOUT -
WE'RE THE MOST FUNCTIONAL

00:31:56.000 --> 00:32:00.000
DYSFUNCTIONAL FAMILY AROUND,
YOU KNOW. STUFF LIKE THAT!

00:32:00.000 --> 00:32:02.000
(laughs)

00:32:11.000 --> 00:32:14.000
IN A TINY RURAL COMMUNITY
 IN SASKATCHEWAN,

00:32:14.000 --> 00:32:16.000
A MAN LOOKING AFTER HIS
 THREE CHILDREN BY HIMSELF

00:32:17.000 --> 00:32:20.000
WAS A NOVELTY. THE CHILDREN
 LEARNED EARLY THAT THEIR

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:23.000
SINGLE FATHER FAMILY
 WAS SOMEHOW DIFFERENT.

00:32:27.000 --> 00:32:30.000
I SAW YOU YESTERDAY.

00:32:30.000 --> 00:32:32.000
YEAH, A LOT OF THE
TEACHERS AND STUFF
WERE KIND OF -

00:32:33.000 --> 00:32:36.000
THERE WERE A FEW THAT
WEREN'T SURE ABOUT IT,
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:39.000
THE MAN DOING THE
COOKING AND THE CLEANING
AND EVERYTHING.

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:41.000
AND THEY JUST THOUGHT
THAT WASN'T RIGHT,
AND IT'S A FAIRLY

00:32:41.000 --> 00:32:44.000
OLD-FASHIONED THINKING
IN MARTENSVILLE, SO...

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:48.000
SOME OF THE KIDS TELL ME THAT
THEIR PARENTS WANT TO, LIKE,

00:32:48.000 --> 00:32:51.000
STAY TOGETHER, UNTIL THE KID'S
OUT. BECAUSE THEY DON'T WANNA

00:32:51.000 --> 00:32:54.000
LIKE - THEY THINK THAT IT'LL
RUIN THEIR LIVES OR SOMETHING.

00:32:54.000 --> 00:32:58.000
SO THEY JUST IGNORE EACH OTHER
TOTALLY, BUT THEY STAY TOGETHER.

00:32:58.000 --> 00:33:01.000
AND THAT'S KIND OF WEIRD.

00:33:01.000 --> 00:33:05.000
A LOT OF PEOPLE THOUGHT
IT WAS WEIRD THAT I WAS
LIVING WITH MY DAD AND

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:08.000
NOT MY MOM. BECAUSE
USUALLY YOU DON'T
LIVE WITH YOUR DAD.

00:33:08.000 --> 00:33:11.000
I THINK HAVING ONE PARENT'S A
LOT BETTER THAN HAVING TWO,

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:14.000
ACTUALLY. 'CAUSE MOST OF MY
FRIENDS - BEFORE THEY CAN SLEEP

00:33:14.000 --> 00:33:16.000
OVER, THEY HAVE TO TALK TO
THEIR MOM AND THEIR DAD.

00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:19.000
AND I JUST TALK TO MY DAD AND
HE SAYS "YES" TO EVERYTHING, SO!

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:23.000
I'M BASICALLY ALLOWED
TO DO LOTS OF STUFF.

00:33:23.000 --> 00:33:26.000
SOME STUFF HE DOESN'T LET ME DO
THOUGH, LIKE IF IT'S JUST GOING

00:33:26.000 --> 00:33:29.000
OVER THE LINE, HE
WON'T LET ME DO IT.

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:33.000
(knocking on the door)

00:33:42.000 --> 00:33:43.000
BYE DAD.

00:33:43.000 --> 00:33:45.000
(Ross) SEE YA!

00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:50.000
WHAT ARE YOU GOING
TO DO IF YOU'RE
LOCKED OUT?

00:33:51.000 --> 00:33:52.000
I DUNNO.

00:33:52.000 --> 00:33:55.000
(Shannon) I THINK IT'S REALLY
FUN LIVING IN MARTENSVILLE.

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:59.000
'CAUSE IT'S LIKE, I HAVE A
LOT OF FRIENDS NOW AND...

00:33:59.000 --> 00:34:03.000
EVERYBODY'S ALWAYS PHONING ME
AND STUFF. SOME... I'M A GOOD

00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:10.000
PEER MEDIATOR. PEER MEDIATOR IS
SOMEBODY THAT LIKE WALKS AROUND

00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:13.000
THE SCHOOL GROUNDS AND HELPS
ANYBODY IF THEY'RE HAVING

00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:16.000
TROUBLES THAT THEY CAN'T SOLVE
FOR THEMSELVES. THEN WE TAKE

00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:20.000
THEM INTO A ROOM, IT'S KINDA
LIKE COUNSELLING. YOU GET TO

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:25.000
KNOW HOW TO SOLVE YOUR OWN
PROBLEMS WITHOUT HAVING TO LIKE,

00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:28.000
BEAT THE CRAP OUTTA EACH OTHER
OR SOMETHING. EVEN THOUGH I'M

00:34:29.000 --> 00:34:32.000
USUALLY NOT THE FIRST ONE TO
CALL UP AND SAY I'M SORRY.

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:37.000
WELL, YOU CAN'T SIT DOWN AND
BE "WELL, WHAT ABOUT MY LIFE?

00:34:37.000 --> 00:34:39.000
WHAT ABOUT MY LIFE?" WELL,
THE HELL WITH YOUR LIFE.

00:34:39.000 --> 00:34:42.000
YOU DO WHAT IT TAKES SO
THEY CAN HAVE A LIFE.

00:34:42.000 --> 00:34:45.000
YOU KNOW - NO MATTER
WHAT IT TAKES.

00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:51.000
OKAY, SHANNY, SEE IF
YOU CAN GET THAT IN YOU.

00:34:51.000 --> 00:34:52.000
THEN YOU CAN
TAKE OFF.

00:34:53.000 --> 00:34:55.000
DO YOUR
HOMEWORK AFTER.

00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:57.000
YOU DON'T HAVE
MUCH, RIGHT?

00:34:57.000 --> 00:34:59.000
NO. I ONLY HAVE
TWO QUESTIONS.

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:01.000
PSHAW. YOU GOTTA
EAT SOME OF THAT.

00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:03.000
I ALREADY ATE
SOME OF THAT.

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:07.000
(Caroline) ROSS IS UM... HARD
AND TOUGH ON THE OUTSIDE,

00:35:07.000 --> 00:35:14.000
BUT A BIG SOFT MARSHMALLOW
IN THE MIDDLE. HE'S UM...

00:35:14.000 --> 00:35:17.000
KIND OF A MACHO KIND OF A GUY
UNTIL YOU GET TO KNOW HIM.

00:35:17.000 --> 00:35:20.000
HE'S REALLY A GENTLE SOUL.

00:35:20.000 --> 00:35:21.000
HAD ENOUGH?

00:35:21.000 --> 00:35:22.000
YEAH.

00:35:22.000 --> 00:35:24.000
OKAY. TAKE OFF.
9:30, OKAY?

00:35:24.000 --> 00:35:26.000
UH HUH.

00:35:26.000 --> 00:35:27.000
WELL, WAIT - 9.

00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:30.000
I'M NOT GOING TO
BED AT 9:30!

00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:32.000
I KNOW, BUT YOU'RE DOING
YOUR TWO QUESTIONS.

00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:34.000
IT DOESN'T TAKE ME HALF
AN HOUR TO DO MY HOMEWORK.

00:35:34.000 --> 00:35:35.000
FINE. 9:30.

00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:36.000
THANK YOU!

00:35:36.000 --> 00:35:37.000
SEE YA.

00:35:37.000 --> 00:35:38.000
BYE.

00:35:38.000 --> 00:35:39.000
BE GOOD.

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:40.000
I WILL.

00:35:42.000 --> 00:35:44.000
FOR FOUR AND A HALF YEARS
 ROSS STRUGGLED TO KEEP

00:35:44.000 --> 00:35:48.000
HIS FAMILY TOGETHER,
 BUT THEN A BOMBSHELL.

00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:50.000
(Jessica) ME AND DAD WEREN'T
GETTING ALONG VERY WELL...

00:35:50.000 --> 00:35:55.000
I FIGURED, THOUGHT
MAYBE TAKING SOME TIME
APART WOULD BE A GOOD

00:35:55.000 --> 00:36:01.000
DECISION - GETTING TO
KNOW MOM BETTER AND...
MAYBE THAT WOULD BE GOOD.

00:36:01.000 --> 00:36:05.000
JUSTIN AND JESSICA, THE
 TWO ELDEST CHILDREN,

00:36:05.000 --> 00:36:08.000
DECIDED IT WAS TIME TO MOVE
 BACK IN WITH THEIR MOTHER.

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:15.000
I HAD TO GET USED TO THE IDEA
THAT THEY'RE GOING TO LEAVE.

00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:18.000
THEY'VE GOT THEIR OWN
BRAINS, I CAN'T STOP THEM.

00:36:18.000 --> 00:36:21.000
THE YEARS I'VE HAD THEM,
I'VE TRIED TO SHOW THEM THE

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:23.000
DIFFERENCE BETWEEN RIGHT AND
WRONG AND TO BE INDEPENDENT

00:36:23.000 --> 00:36:25.000
THINKERS AND NOW
THEY'RE THINKING.

00:36:25.000 --> 00:36:28.000
IT'S WHAT I TAUGHT THEM TO DO.

00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:33.000
IN THE WINTER AFTER HER
 BROTHER AND SISTER HAD GONE,

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:35.000
SHANNON DEVELOPED
 HEALTH PROBLEMS.

00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:38.000
SHE WAS THIN, AND HAD
 DIFFICULTY EATING.

00:36:38.000 --> 00:36:40.000
AFTER NUMEROUS MEDICAL
 APPOINTMENTS, THERE WERE STILL

00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:43.000
NO DIAGNOSIS AND
 ROSS WAS WORRIED.

00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:52.000
ENDED UP WITH
ANOTHER
PRESCRIPTION?

00:36:52.000 --> 00:36:54.000
UH HUH

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:56.000
I'M BEGINNING TO WONDER
IF THOSE PILLS YOU'RE TAKING

00:36:57.000 --> 00:37:00.000
AREN'T GIVING YOU
A STOMACH ACHE TOO.

00:37:13.000 --> 00:37:16.000
OVER THE LONG PRAIRIE WINTER
 THINGS GOT WORSE FOR ROSS.

00:37:16.000 --> 00:37:18.000
MONEY WAS TIGHTER THAN EVER.

00:37:18.000 --> 00:37:22.000
SHANNON WAS NOW A TEENAGER,
 EXPENSES WERE HIGHER.

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:27.000
YOU GOTTA EAT
TWO, COME OFF IT,
TRY AND EAT TWO.

00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:31.000
THE CAR NEEDED WORK,
MY PLATES WERE DUE.

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:36.000
JANUARY AND FEBRUARY AND STUFF
IS A BAD MONTH FOR ME,

00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:38.000
JUST EVERYTHING.

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:41.000
SHANNY HAD NO CLOTHES TO WEAR
ANYMORE - SHE GREW ABOUT A FOOT.

00:37:41.000 --> 00:37:44.000
I WAS JUST WONDERING
WHAT HAPPENS NEXT, EH.

00:37:44.000 --> 00:37:46.000
IT'S LIKE WHEN YOU GOT NO
CONTROL OVER YOUR LIFE,

00:37:46.000 --> 00:37:49.000
EVERYBODY ELSE IS PULLING THE
STRINGS AND YOU JUST KIND OF

00:37:49.000 --> 00:37:52.000
SIT THERE AND WONDER WHAT'S
GOING TO HAPPEN NEXT, EH.

00:37:52.000 --> 00:37:54.000
WHAT ARE WE DOING
THIS SUMMER MAYBE?

00:37:55.000 --> 00:37:56.000
I DUNNO.

00:37:56.000 --> 00:37:57.000
MOVING?

00:37:57.000 --> 00:37:59.000
YEAH.

00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:00.000
WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT THAT?

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:02.000
I DON'T CARE.

00:38:02.000 --> 00:38:04.000
TRY AND BE
NICE, OKAY?

00:38:04.000 --> 00:38:06.000
I AM, BUT I DON'T CARE.

00:38:09.000 --> 00:38:12.000
HE DECIDED TO MOVE OUT OF
 MARTENSVILLE AND SHARE AN

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:14.000
APARTMENT WITH HIS FRIEND,
 CAROLINE, IN SASKATOON,

00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:18.000
A FEW KILOMETRES AWAY. BY THE
 SPRING, SHANNON'S ILLNESS

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:21.000
WAS UNDER CONTROL, AND SHE
 WAS SLOWLY RECOVERING.

00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:25.000
BY MID SUMMER IT SEEMED THAT
 LIFE WAS FINALLY TURNING AROUND

00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:28.000
FOR ROSS HEIGHT. THE
 RELATIONSHIP WITH CAROLINE

00:38:28.000 --> 00:38:31.000
HAD DEEPENED AND HE NOW HAD A
 WELL PAYING JOB CAT SKINNING

00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:33.000
FOR THE OIL PATCH.

00:38:34.000 --> 00:38:37.000
(Ross) IT'S FAMILIAR STUFF
AND I ENJOY DOING IT.

00:38:37.000 --> 00:38:40.000
ACTUALLY, I'M VERY GLAD TO
BE DOING IT AGAIN INSTEAD OF

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:44.000
COOPED UP IN SHOPS OR SITTING
AROUND WATCHING TV.

00:38:44.000 --> 00:38:48.000
THE WAY IT WORKS, YOU GO AWAY
FOR A COUPLE OF WEEKS AND YOU

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:51.000
COME HOME FOR A FEW
DAYS OR WHATEVER.

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:55.000
WHEN THERE'S WORK TO DO, YOU DO
IT, BUT YOU HAVE TO BE MOBILE.

00:38:55.000 --> 00:38:59.000
NOW I CAN BE MOBILE, UNLIKE THE
LAST SEVERAL YEARS WITH THE

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:02.000
KIDS. FIVE YEARS AGO, OR THREE
YEARS AGO EVEN, LOOKING FIVE

00:39:03.000 --> 00:39:05.000
MINUTES AHEAD WAS KIND OF
HARD ON THE HEAD!

00:39:05.000 --> 00:39:07.000
DIDN'T WANT TO THINK ABOUT IT.

00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:10.000
IT'S NICE TO BE ALIVE
AGAIN, THAT'S FOR SURE.

00:39:10.000 --> 00:39:12.000
BUT THERE WAS TENSION.

00:39:12.000 --> 00:39:14.000
FOR SHANNON, NOW 15, THERE'S
 A DIFFICULT DECISION ON

00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:17.000
THE HORIZON, SHE HAD BEEN
 VISITING HER OLDER BROTHER

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:20.000
AND SISTER AND WAS BEING
 PRESSURED TO MOVE TO

00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:23.000
VANCOUVER. ROSS HEIGHT
 FEARED HE WOULD SOON LOSE

00:39:23.000 --> 00:39:25.000
HIS THIRD CHILD.

00:39:25.000 --> 00:39:28.000
(Ross) SHANNY WAS OUT THERE FOR
A WEEK AND I COULD TELL WHEN

00:39:28.000 --> 00:39:30.000
SHANNON GOT BACK THAT
SHE WAS A DIFFERENT GIRL.

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:33.000
AND THEY WERE TRYING TO
CONVINCE HER AGAIN, STILL,

00:39:33.000 --> 00:39:36.000
THAT THERE WAS SOMETHING WRONG
WITH THE ENVIRONMENT SHE WAS IN

00:39:36.000 --> 00:39:38.000
IN SASKATOON.

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:43.000
DAD GOES AWAY, RIGHT,
AND HE GOES AWAY FOR
LIKE TWO OR THREE WEEKS

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:46.000
AT A TIME. AND SHE
DOESN'T SEE HIM
FOR THAT LONG AND

00:39:46.000 --> 00:39:49.000
SHE STAYS WITH HIS
GIRLFRIEND AND...
I DON'T KNOW.

00:39:49.000 --> 00:39:52.000
I THINK SHE'S JUST
CRAZY AND SHE WANTS
MORE OF HER ACTUAL

00:39:52.000 --> 00:39:54.000
FAMILY AROUND.

00:39:54.000 --> 00:39:56.000
IT'S GOOD TO HAVE FAMILY.

00:39:56.000 --> 00:40:00.000
THE DECISION HE'S BEEN DREADING
 IS ABOUT TO BECOME A REALITY.

00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:03.000
AFTER LIVING WITH HER FATHER
 AND CAROLINE IN THE NEW

00:40:03.000 --> 00:40:05.000
APARTMENT, SHANNON ANNOUNCED
 THAT SHE'D MADE ARRANGEMENTS TO

00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:09.000
MOVE IN WITH HER MOTHER AND
 ATTEND SCHOOL IN VANCOUVER.

00:40:09.000 --> 00:40:17.000
(*)

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:22.000
I DON'T THINK SHE'S OKAY. I
DON'T THINK THINGS WILL EVER BE

00:40:22.000 --> 00:40:26.000
OKAY OUT THERE, BUT THERE'S
NOTHING I CAN DO ABOUT IT.

00:40:26.000 --> 00:40:31.000
AND ON THE OTHER HAND, YOU
KNOW, AM I SUPPOSED TO SPEND

00:40:31.000 --> 00:40:34.000
THE NEXT 20 YEARS
FIGHTING THIS THING TOO?

00:40:34.000 --> 00:40:37.000
EVENTUALLY IT'S GOING TO HAVE
TO BE UP TO THEM TO DECIDE

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:41.000
WHICH, WHAT KIND OF
